# Documented CVE exceptions for users-service
# Each entry MUST include: CVE ID, package, severity, justification, review date
#
# CVE-2026-33671 - picomatch ReDoS
# Package: picomatch (transitive via nodemon -> chokidar -> anymatch/readdirp)
# Severity: HIGH
# Justification: nodemon is a devDependency only, not present in production runtime image.
#                The vulnerable picomatch is only used at dev-time for file watching.
#                Production image is built with --omit=dev so this dep isn't shipped.
# Risk: None — code path is not reachable in deployed image.
# Review: 2026-07-10
CVE-2026-33671

# CVE-2026-22184 - zlib arbitrary code execution via untgz utility
# Package: zlib (alpine OS layer, included in node:22-alpine base image)
# Severity: CRITICAL
# Justification: Vulnerability is in untgz utility which is not invoked at runtime.
#                Service does not extract tar/gzip archives. Awaiting upstream alpine fix.
# Risk: Low — code path is not reachable from application code.
# Review: 2026-05-10
CVE-2026-22184

# CVE-2026-28390 - OpenSSL DoS via NULL pointer dereference in CMS
# Package: libcrypto3, libssl3 (alpine OS layer)
# Severity: HIGH
# Justification: Awaiting upstream alpine package update. Service does not parse
#                arbitrary CMS messages from untrusted input. TLS termination
#                happens at the ingress, not in this service.
# Risk: Low — code path requires malicious CMS payload which is not exposed.
# Review: 2026-05-10
CVE-2026-28390
